th of ex-premier De Gasperi will probably have little immediate effect on the policies of the Italian government, but it may later result in new efforts to dissolve the present coalition. Although De Gasperi had turned over the post of secretary general of the Christian Democratic Party to Amintore Fanfani in June, he remained the major influence for harmony between Fanfani's left-wing group and the party's center. De Gasperi was also largely responsible for the maintenance of the alliance--criticized on occasions by Fanfani--between the Christian Democrats and the three minor center parties.\n\nFanfani is believed to favor a single-party government. Rightist elements in the Christian Democratic Party are known to desire a coalition with the Monarchists, while some elements in the party are known to favor an arrangement with the Communist-allied Nenni Socialists", "token_count": 144, "token_end_0based": 143, "token_start_0based": 0, "token_text": "7 comment on death of alcide de gasperi the death of ex-premier de gasperi will probably have little immediate effect on the policies of the italian government but it may later result in new efforts to dissolve the present coalition although de gasperi had turned over the post of secretary general of the christian democratic party to amintore fanfani in june he remained the major influence for harmony between fanfani's left-wing group and the party's center de gasperi was also largely responsible for the maintenance of the alliance criticized on occasions by fanfani between the christian democrats and the three minor center parties fanfani is believed to favor a single-party government rightist elements in the christian democratic party are known to desire a coalition with the monarchists while some elements in the party are known to favor an arrangement with the communist-allied nenni socialists", "unred_source_page": 7}
